choices.text: the signing of the Comprehensive Peace Agreement (CPA) in 2005. The CPA ended the 21-year civil war between the North and the South. The CPA was signed by the Sudan People’s Liberation Movement (SPLM) and the National Congress Party (NCP) in the presence of the international community. The CPA was a milestone in the history of Sudan. It was the first time that the two parties signed a peace agreement. The CPA was a result of the efforts of the international community, especially the United States of America, the United Kingdom, Norway, and the African Union.
